Difference between Images and Container:
Container is a running environment for IMAGE
Port Binded : talk to application running inside of container. ( 5000 )
Virtual file system.

1. docker pull <image_name>
2. docker images
3. docker name <image_name>
4. docker run -d <image_name> : ID
5. docker ps : List of all the images working 
6. docker stop <image_id>
7. docker ps -a : history (lists running and stopped container)
8. docker run -p<host_port>:<container_port> 

DIFFERENCE BETWEEN PORT AND HOST PORT
-------------------------------------
1. Multiple containers can run on your host machine
2. Laptop has only certain ports available, need to create so-caalled binding b/w a poert that your laptop your host machine and container.

